    <briefdescription>
<para>The dynamic property info. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>A callback of the following type may be used: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">Property::Value<sp/>MyFunction(int32_t<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">id</highlight><highlight class="normal">,<sp/>VectorAnimationRenderer::VectorProperty<sp/><ref refid="structDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelAnimatedVectorImageVisual_1_1DynamicPropertyInfo_1a1bfca27e4b5fd47c1915cb755f14f875" kindref="member">property</ref>,<sp/>uint32_t<sp/>frameNumber);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
</simplesect>
id The id to specify the callback. property The property that represent what you are trying to change. frameNumber The current frame number. It returns a Property::Value to set according to the property type.</para>
<para>The callback will be called on the worker thread. You MUST not call other DALi methods in the callback. And the object must still be alive when the callback occurs if you make the callback from a class member function. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
